data.description: Accept End User Terms and Conditions. Accepting Terms can be implemented as part of creating a user or as a separate step.
data.name: Accept Terms and Conditions

data.description: Cancel the Offering. This will only work if the logged-in User is a team member of the Organization for this Offering. It will not work unless the Offering has status as Draft or Submitted.
data.name: Cancel the Offering

data.description: Check that your network has been set up and is available through the API with your API key.
data.name: Check the status of your network

data.description: Create a new Offering for this Organization. The logged-in User must be a team member of this Organization.
data.name: Create a new Offering for this Organization

data.description: Create a new Organization.
data.name: Create a new Organization

data.description: Check the current health status of the Crowd Valley API.
data.name: Crowd Valley API health status

data.description: Delete the Organization from the network. This will only work if the logged-in User is a team member of the Organization. It will not work if the Organization has any Offerings that do not have status as Canceled.
data.name: Delete the Organization from this network

data.description: Information about this Investment. It will only work if the Investment has visibility set to Open or Anonymous.
data.name: Information about this Investment

data.description: Information about this Offering. This will only work if the Offering is visible in the network.
data.name: Information about this Offering

data.description: Populate a list of Investments for this Offering. This can be used to show a list of current investors for this Offering. Investments will be shown in full if visibility is set to Open.
data.name: List of Investments for this Offering

data.description: Populate a live Offerings page or a historical/closed deals page. Visible Offerings are those with status Restricted, Published, Live, Closing or Settled.
data.name: List of Offerings

data.description: Populate information on an user's private account page.
data.name: Logged-in user's account information

data.description: Register a new User. Implement this as part of your registration form, including as much information as you want to collect on the first form. User information can be changed or adjusted later using the 'self' endpoint.
data.name: Register a new User

data.description: A list of visible Organizations in the network. Implement this to show a list of Organizations that are supporting various deals, or that are umbrella entities for various users. This will only show Organizations that have visibility set to Open.
data.name: Retrieve a list of Organizations

data.description: Populate a user's public profile information. Implement this to allow the logged-in user to see information about other users on the network. It will only populate all information if the target user's visibility is set to Open. This function will only show public profile information - it will not show private account information.
data.name: Retrieve a User's public profile information

data.description: Information about the Organization. This will only work if the logged-in User is a team member of the Organization or the Organization has visibility set to Open.
data.name: Retrieve information about this Organization

data.description: A list of visible Offerings for this Organization. Visible Offerings are those with status Restricted, Published, Live, Closing or Settled.
data.name: Retrieve Offerings for this Organization

data.description: Retrieve a list of the user's investments. This will include open investment offers as well as closed investments.
data.name: Retrieve the user's investments

data.description: Submit an Investment for this Offering. This can be used to implement an 'Invest' button on an Offering's page.
data.name: Submit an Investment

data.description: A list of the logged-in User's Organizations. This could be used to show for which Organization(s) the User works or for which Organization(s) the User has created Offerings.
data.name: The User's Organizations

data.description: Update the logged-in user's profile information.
data.name: Update a user's profile information

data.description: Update this Investment. The Investment must have been made by the logged-in User.
data.name: Update an Investment

data.description: Update the Offering's information. This will only work if the logged-in User is a team member of the Organization for this Offering and the Offering status is Draft.
data.name: Update the Offering's information

data.description: Update the Organization's information. This will only work if the logged-in User is a team member of the Organization.
data.name: Update the Organization's information

data.description: Populate a public listing page of your visible Users. Users are visible if they have their Visibility field set to Open.
data.name: Visible Users in your network

data.description: Withdraw this Investment. The Investment must have been made by the logged-in User.
data.name: Withdraw this Investment

description:
The Crowd Valley API is used to build online platforms and marketplaces globally for managing private placements, securities, real estate, crowdfunding, peer-to-peer lending, and public stock trading.

The public REST API provides an end to end server side application, which supports the technical back office requirements for client side applications of various kinds in the online investing and lending markets.

The Crowd Valley API also contains private financial back office functions and other services which are made available on request.
name: v1
